      <Math mode="display" tex="\begin{split}\displaystyle u_{t}(t,x)&amp;\displaystyle=\partial_{i}\big{(}a_{ij}(%&#10;x)\partial_{j}u(t,x)\big{)}+b_{i}(x)\partial_{i}u(t,x)+c(x)u(t,x)\\&#10;&amp;\displaystyle+\partial_{i}\big{(}\tilde{a}_{ij}(x)\partial_{j}u(t-\tau,x)\big%&#10;{)}+\tilde{b}_{i}(x)\partial_{i}u(t-\tau,x)+\tilde{c}(x)u(t-\tau,x)+\\&#10;&amp;\displaystyle+f(t,x)\text{ for }(t,x)\in(0,\infty)\times\Omega,\\&#10;\displaystyle u(t,x)&amp;\displaystyle=\gamma(t,x)\text{ for }(t,x)\in(0,\infty)%&#10;\times\partial\Omega,\\&#10;\displaystyle u(0,x)&amp;\displaystyle=u^{0}(x)\text{ for }x\in\Omega,\\&#10;\displaystyle u(t,x)&amp;\displaystyle=\varphi(t,x)\text{ for }(t,x)\in(-\tau,0)%&#10;\times\Omega.\end{split}" text="formulae@(u _ t * open-interval@(t, x) = (partial-differential _ i)@(a _ (i * j) * x * (partial-differential _ j)@(u) * open-interval@(t, x)) + b _ i * x * (partial-differential _ i)@(u) * open-interval@(t, x) + c * x * u * open-interval@(t, x) + (partial-differential _ i)@((tilde@(a)) _ (i * j) * x * (partial-differential _ j)@(u) * open-interval@(t - tau, x)) + (tilde@(b)) _ i * x * (partial-differential _ i)@(u) * open-interval@(t - tau, x) + tilde@(c) * x * u * open-interval@(t - tau, x) + f * open-interval@(t, x) * [ for ] * open-interval@(t, x) element-of open-interval@(0, infinity) * Omega, u * open-interval@(t, x) = gamma * open-interval@(t, x) * [ for ] * open-interval@(t, x) element-of open-interval@(0, infinity) * partial-differential@(Omega), u * open-interval@(0, x) = u ^ 0 * x * [ for ] * x element-of Omega, u * open-interval@(t, x) = varphi * open-interval@(t, x) * [ for ] * open-interval@(t, x) element-of open-interval@(- tau, 0) * Omega)" xml:id="S0.Ex4.m1">

    <equation xml:id="S0.Ex5">
      <Math mode="display" tex="\begin{split}\displaystyle\partial_{tt}u(t,x)-\triangle u(t,x)+a_{0}\partial_{%&#10;t}u(t,x)+a\partial_{t}u(t-\tau,x)&amp;\displaystyle=0\text{ for }(t,x)\in(0,\infty%&#10;)\times\Omega,\\&#10;\displaystyle u(t,x)&amp;\displaystyle=0\text{ for }(t,x)\in(0,\infty)\times\Gamma%&#10;_{0},\\&#10;\displaystyle\frac{\partial u}{\partial\nu}(t,x)&amp;\displaystyle=0\text{ for }(t%&#10;,x)\in(0,\infty)\times\Gamma_{1}\end{split}" text="formulae@(((partial-differential _ (t * t))@(u) * open-interval@(t, x) - triangle * u * open-interval@(t, x)) + a _ 0 * (partial-differential _ t)@(u) * open-interval@(t, x) + a * (partial-differential _ t)@(u) * open-interval@(t - tau, x) = 0 * [ for ] * open-interval@(t, x) element-of open-interval@(0, infinity) * Omega, u * open-interval@(t, x) = 0 * [ for ] * open-interval@(t, x) element-of open-interval@(0, infinity) * Gamma _ 0, (partial-differential@(u) / partial-differential@(nu)) * open-interval@(t, x) = 0 * [ for ] * open-interval@(t, x) element-of open-interval@(0, infinity) * Gamma _ 1)" xml:id="S0.Ex5.m1">

    <equation xml:id="S0.Ex6">
      <Math mode="display" tex="\begin{split}\displaystyle\partial_{tt}u(t,x)&amp;\displaystyle=a^{2}\partial_{xx}%&#10;u(t-\tau,x)+b\partial_{x}u(t-\tau,x)+cu(t-\tau,x)\\&#10;&amp;\displaystyle+f(t,x)\text{ for }(t,x)\in(0,T)\times(0,l),\\&#10;\displaystyle u(t,x)&amp;\displaystyle=\gamma(t,x)\text{ for }(t,x)\in(0,T)\times%&#10;\{0,1\},\\&#10;\displaystyle u(0,x)&amp;\displaystyle=u^{0}(x)\text{ for }x\in(0,1),\\&#10;\displaystyle u(t,x)&amp;\displaystyle=\varphi(t,x)\text{ for }t\in(-\tau,0),x\in(%&#10;0,1).\end{split}" text="formulae@((partial-differential _ (t * t))@(u) * open-interval@(t, x) = a ^ 2 * (partial-differential _ (x * x))@(u) * open-interval@(t - tau, x) + b * (partial-differential _ x)@(u) * open-interval@(t - tau, x) + c * u * open-interval@(t - tau, x) + f * open-interval@(t, x) * [ for ] * open-interval@(t, x) element-of open-interval@(0, T) * open-interval@(0, l), u * open-interval@(t, x) = gamma * open-interval@(t, x) * [ for ] * open-interval@(t, x) element-of open-interval@(0, T) * set@(0, 1), u * open-interval@(0, x) = u ^ 0 * x * [ for ] * x element-of open-interval@(0, 1), u * open-interval@(t, x) = varphi * open-interval@(t, x) * [ for ] * t element-of open-interval@(- tau, 0), x element-of open-interval@(0, 1))" xml:id="S0.Ex6.m1">

  <para xml:id="p14">
    <equation xml:id="S0.Ex7">
      <Math mode="display" tex="\begin{split}\displaystyle\partial_{tt}u(x,t)-a\partial_{xx}u(x,t-\tau)+b%&#10;\partial_{x}\theta(x,t-\tau)&amp;\displaystyle=f(x,t)\text{ for }x\in\Omega,t&gt;0,\\&#10;\displaystyle\partial_{t}\theta(x,t)-c\partial_{xx}\theta(x,t-\tau)+d\partial_%&#10;{tx}u(x,t-\tau)&amp;\displaystyle=g(x,t)\text{ for }x\in\Omega,t&gt;0,\\&#10;\displaystyle }t&gt;0,\\&#10;\displaystyle\phantom{\partial_{t}}u(x,0)=u^{0}(x),\quad\phantom{\partial_{t}}%&#10;u(x,t)&amp;\displaystyle=u^{0}(x,t)\text{ for }x\in\Omega,t\in(-\tau,0),\\&#10;\displaystyle\partial_{t}u(x,0)=u^{1}(x),\quad\partial_{t}u(x,t)&amp;\displaystyle%&#10;=u^{1}(x,t)\text{ for }x\in\Omega,t\in(-\tau,0),\\&#10;\displaystyle\phantom{\partial_{t}}\theta(x,0)=\theta^{0}(x),\quad\phantom{%&#10;\partial_{t}}\theta(x,t)&amp;\displaystyle=\theta^{0}(x,t)\text{ for     <equation xml:id="S0.Ex14">
      <Math mode="display" tex="\begin{split}\displaystyle c_{1}(s)&amp;\displaystyle=\left(\det{}_{L(X)}\begin{%&#10;pmatrix}e^{\Omega s}&amp;e^{-\Omega s}\\&#10;\Omega e^{\Omega s}&amp;-\Omega e^{-\Omega s}\end{pmatrix}\right)^{-1}\det{}_{L(X)%&#10;}\begin{pmatrix}0_{L(X)}&amp;e^{-\Omega s}\\&#10;\mathrm{id}_{X}&amp;-\Omega e^{-\Omega s}\end{pmatrix}=\tfrac{1}{2}\Omega^{-1}e^{-%&#10;\Omega s},\\&#10;\displaystyle c_{2}(s)&amp;\displaystyle=\left(\det{}_{L(X)}\begin{pmatrix}e^{%&#10;\Omega s}&amp;e^{-\Omega s}\\&#10;\Omega e^{\Omega s}&amp;-\Omega e^{-\Omega s}\end{pmatrix}\right)^{-1}\det{}_{L(X)%&#10;}\begin{pmatrix}e^{\Omega s}&amp;0_{L(X)}\\&#10;\Omega e^{\Omega s}&amp;\mathrm{id}_{X}\end{pmatrix}=\tfrac{1}{2}\Omega^{-1}e^{-%&#10;\Omega s}.\end{split}" text="formulae@(c _ 1 * s = (determinant@(_ L * X matrix[[e ^ (Omega * s), e ^ (- Omega * s)], [Omega * e ^ (Omega * s), - Omega * e ^ (- Omega * s)]])) ^ (- 1) * determinant@(_ L * X matrix[[0 _ (L * X), e ^ (- Omega * s)], [id _ X, - Omega * e ^ (- Omega * s)]]) = (1 / 2) * Omega ^ (- 1) * e ^ (- Omega * s), c _ 2 * s = (determinant@(_ L * X matrix[[e ^ (Omega * s), e ^ (- Omega * s)], [Omega * e ^ (Omega * s), - Omega * e ^ (- Omega * s)]])) ^ (- 1) * determinant@(_ L * X matrix[[e ^ (Omega * s), 0 _ (L * X)], [Omega * e ^ (Omega * s), id _ X]]) = (1 / 2) * Omega ^ (- 1) * e ^ (- Omega * s))" xml:id="S0.Ex14.m1">

    <equation labels="LABEL:EQUATION_HARMONIC_OSCILLATOR_GENERAL_EXPLICIT_SOLUTION" xml:id="S0.E14">
      <tags>
        <tag>(14)</tag>
        <tag role="autoref">Equation 14</tag>
        <tag role="refnum">14</tag>
      </tags>
      <Math mode="display" tex="\begin{split}\displaystyle x(t)&amp;\displaystyle=\tfrac{1}{2}(e^{\Omega t}+e^{-%&#10;\Omega t})x_{0}+\tfrac{1}{2}\Omega^{-1}(e^{\Omega t}-e^{-\Omega t})x_{1}\\&#10;&amp;\displaystyle+\tfrac{1}{2}\Omega^{-1}\int_{0}^{t}(e^{\Omega(t-s)}-e^{-\Omega(%&#10;t-s)})f(s)\mathrm{d}s\text{ for }t\geq 0.\end{split}" text="x * t = (1 / 2) * (e ^ (Omega * t) + e ^ (- Omega * t)) * x _ 0 + (1 / 2) * Omega ^ (- 1) * (e ^ (Omega * t) - e ^ (- Omega * t)) * x _ 1 + (1 / 2) * Omega ^ (- 1) * ((integral _ 0) ^ t)@((e ^ (Omega * (t - s)) - e ^ (- Omega * (t - s))) * f * s * differential-d@(s) * [ for ] * t) &gt;= 0" xml:id="S0.E14.m1">

    <equation labels="LABEL:EQUATION_DIFFERENCE_EQUATION_FOR_DOT_X_N" xml:id="S0.E19">
      <tags>
        <tag>(19)</tag>

      <Math mode="display" tex="\begin{split}\displaystyle\dot{x}_{n}(s)&amp;\displaystyle=\dot{x}_{n-1}(0)+\Omega%&#10;^{2}x_{n-1}(s)+\int_{2(n-1)\tau}^{2(n-1)\tau+s}f(\sigma)\mathrm{d}\sigma\text{%&#10; for }s\in[-2\tau,0],n\in\mathbb{N},\\&#10;\displaystyle x_{0}(s)&amp;\displaystyle=\varphi(s)\text{ for }s\in[-2\tau,0].\end%&#10;{split}" text="formulae@((dot@(x)) _ n * s = (dot@(x)) _ (n - 1) * 0 + Omega ^ 2 * x _ (n - 1) * s + ((integral _ (2 * (n - 1) * tau)) ^ (2 * (n - 1) * tau + s))@(f * sigma * differential-d@(sigma) * [ for ] * s) element-of closed-interval@(- 2 * tau, 0), formulae@(n element-of N, x _ 0 * s = varphi * s * [ for ] * s element-of closed-interval@(- 2 * tau, 0)))" xml:id="S0.E19.m1">

    <equation labels="LABEL:EQUATION_DEFINITION_OF_DELAYED_EXPONENTIAL" xml:id="S0.E26">
      <tags>
        <tag>(26)</tag>

        <tag role="refnum">26</tag>
      </tags>
      <Math mode="display" tex="\exp_{\tau}(t;\Omega):=\left\{\begin{array}[]{cc}0_{L(X)},&amp;-\infty&lt;t&lt;-\tau,\\&#10;\mathrm{id}_{X},&amp;-\tau\leq t&lt;0,\\&#10;\mathrm{id}_{X}+\Omega\frac{t}{1!},&amp;0\leq t&lt;\tau,\\&#10;\mathrm{id}_{X}+\Omega\frac{t}{1!}+\Omega^{2}\frac{(t-\tau)^{2}}{2!},&amp;\tau\leq&#10;t%&#10;&lt;2\tau,\\&#10;\dots&amp;\dots\\&#10;\mathrm{id}_{X}+\Omega\frac{t}{1!}+\Omega^{2}\frac{(t-\tau)^{2}}{2!}+\dots+%&#10;\Omega^{k}\frac{\left(t-(k-1)\tau\right)^{k}}{k!},&amp;(k-1)\tau\leq t&lt;k\tau,\\&#10;\dots&amp;\dots.\end{array}\right." text="(exponential _ tau)@(t, Omega) assign cases@(Array[[0 _ (L * X), - infinity less t less - tau], [id _ X, - tau less= t less 0], [id _ X + Omega * (t / 1factorial), 0 less= t less tau], [id _ X + Omega * (t / 1factorial) + Omega ^ 2 * ((t - tau) ^ 2 / 2factorial), tau less= t less 2 * tau], [dots, dots], [id _ X + Omega * (t / 1factorial) + Omega ^ 2 * ((t - tau) ^ 2 / 2factorial) + dots + Omega ^ k * ((t - (k - 1) * tau) ^ k / kfactorial), (k - 1) * tau less= t less k * tau], [dots, dots]])" xml:id="S0.E26.m1">

        <MathFork>
          <Math tex="\displaystyle=\Omega^{2}\exp_{\tau}(t-2\tau;\Omega)=\Omega^{2}x(t-2\tau)." text="absent = Omega ^ 2 * (exponential _ tau)@(t - 2 * tau, Omega) = Omega ^ 2 * x * (t - 2 * tau)" xml:id="S0.Ex35.m3">
            <XMath>
              <XMDual>

    <equation xml:id="S0.Ex38">
      <Math mode="display" tex="x_{2}(t;\Omega)=\left\{\begin{array}[]{cc}0_{L(X)},&amp;-\tau\leq t&lt;0,\\&#10;\mathrm{id}_{X}\frac{t}{1!},&amp;0\leq t&lt;2\tau,\\&#10;\mathrm{id}_{X}\frac{t}{1!}+\Omega^{2}\frac{(t-2\tau)^{3}}{3!},&amp;2\tau\leq t&lt;4%&#10;\tau,\\&#10;\mathrm{id}_{X}\frac{t}{1!}+\Omega^{2}\frac{(t-2\tau)^{3}}{3!}+\Omega^{4}\frac%&#10;{(t-4\tau)^{5}}{5!},&amp;4\tau\leq t&lt;6\tau,\\&#10;\dots&amp;\dots\\&#10;\mathrm{id}_{X}\frac{t}{1!}+\Omega^{2}\frac{(t-2\tau)^{3}}{3!}+\dots+\Omega^{2%&#10;k}\frac{(t-(2k)\tau)^{2k+1}}{(2k+1)!},&amp;2k\tau\leq t&lt;2(k+1)\tau.\end{array}\right." text="x _ 2 * list@(t, Omega) = cases@(Array[[0 _ (L * X), - tau less= t less 0], [id _ X * (t / 1factorial), 0 less= t less 2 * tau], [id _ X * (t / 1factorial) + Omega ^ 2 * ((t - 2 * tau) ^ 3 / 3factorial), 2 * tau less= t less 4 * tau], [id _ X * (t / 1factorial) + Omega ^ 2 * ((t - 2 * tau) ^ 3 / 3factorial) + Omega ^ 4 * ((t - 4 * tau) ^ 5 / 5factorial), 4 * tau less= t less 6 * tau], [dots, dots], [id _ X * (t / 1factorial) + Omega ^ 2 * ((t - 2 * tau) ^ 3 / 3factorial) + dots + Omega ^ (2 * k) * ((t - 2 * k * tau) ^ (2 * k + 1) / (2 * k + 1)factorial), 2 * k * tau less= t less 2 * (k + 1) * tau]])" xml:id="S0.Ex38.m1">

    <equation xml:id="S0.Ex39">
      <Math mode="display" tex="x(t)=x^{1}_{\tau}(t+\tau;\Omega)\varphi(-2\tau)+x^{2}_{\tau}(t+2\tau;\Omega)%&#10;\dot{\varphi}(-2\tau)+\int_{-2\tau}^{0}x^{2}_{\tau}(t-s;\Omega)\ddot{\varphi}(%&#10;s)\mathrm{d}s." text="x * t = (x ^ 1) _ tau * list@(t + tau, Omega) * varphi * (- 2 * tau) + (x ^ 2) _ tau * list@(t + 2 * tau, Omega) * dot@(varphi) * (- 2 * tau) + ((integral _ (- 2 * tau)) ^ 0)@((x ^ 2) _ tau * list@(t - s, Omega) * ddot@(varphi) * s * differential-d@(s))" xml:id="S0.Ex39.m1">
        <XMath>
          <XMDual>
            <XMRef idref="S0.Ex39.m1.6"/>
            <XMWrap>
              <XMApp xml:id="S0.Ex39.m1.6">

        <MathFork>

    <equation xml:id="S0.Ex61">
      <Math mode="display" tex="\begin{split}\displaystyle x(t)&amp;\displaystyle=x^{1}_{\tau}(t+\tau;\Omega)%&#10;\varphi(-2\tau)+x^{2}_{\tau}(t+2\tau;\Omega)\dot{\varphi}(-2\tau)+\int_{-2\tau%&#10;}^{0}x^{2}_{\tau}(t-s;\Omega)\ddot{\varphi}(s)\mathrm{d}s\\&#10;&amp;\displaystyle+\left\{\begin{array}[]{cl}0,&amp;t\in[-2\tau,0),\\&#10;\int_{0}^{t}x^{2}_{\tau}(t-s;\Omega)f(s)\mathrm{d}s,&amp;t\geq 0\end{array}\right.%&#10;\end{split}" text="x * t = (x ^ 1) _ tau * list@(t + tau, Omega) * varphi * (- 2 * tau) + (x ^ 2) _ tau * list@(t + 2 * tau, Omega) * dot@(varphi) * (- 2 * tau) + ((integral _ (- 2 * tau)) ^ 0)@((x ^ 2) _ tau * list@(t - s, Omega) * ddot@(varphi) * s * differential-d@(s)) + cases@(Array[[0, t element-of closed-open-interval@(- 2 * tau, 0)], [((integral _ 0) ^ t)@((x ^ 2) _ tau * list@(t - s, Omega) * f * s * differential-d@(s)), t &gt;= 0]])" xml:id="S0.Ex61.m1">

    <equationgroup class="ltx_eqn_align" xml:id="S0.EGx19">
      <equation xml:id="S0.Ex95">
        <MathFork>
          <Math tex="\displaystyle\|\dot{x}(t;\tau)-\dot{\bar{x}}(t)\|\leq\|\dot{\varphi}(0;\tau)-x%&#10;_{1}\|_{X}+\int_{0}^{t}\|\Omega^{2}x(s-2\tau;\tau)-\Omega^{2}\bar{x}(s)\|_{X}%&#10;\mathrm{d}s" text="norm@(dot@(x) * list@(t, tau) - dot@(bar@(x)) * t) less= (norm@(dot@(varphi) * list@(0, tau) - x _ 1)) _ X + ((integral _ 0) ^ t)@((norm@(Omega ^ 2 * x * list@(s - 2 * tau, tau) - Omega ^ 2 * bar@(x) * s)) _ X * differential-d@(s))" xml:id="S0.Ex95.m3">
            <XMath>
              <XMApp>
                <XMTok meaning="less-than-or-equals" name="leq" role="RELOP">≤</XMTok>
                <XMDual>
                  <XMApp>
                    <XMTok meaning="norm"/>
                    <XMRef idref="S0.Ex95.m3.8"/>
                  </XMApp>
                  <XMWrap>
                    <XMTok meaning="parallel-to" name="||" role="VERTBAR">∥</XMTok>
                    <XMApp xml:id="S0.Ex95.m3.8">
                      <XMTok meaning="minus" role="ADDOP">-</XMTok>
                      <XMApp>
                        <XMTok meaning="times" role="MULOP">⁢</XMTok>
                        <XMApp>
                          <XMTok name="dot" role="OVERACCENT">˙</XMTok>
                          <XMTok font="italic" role="UNKNOWN">x</XMTok>
                        </XMApp>
                        <XMDual>
                          <XMApp>
